prompts.frontCover:
A humorous watercolor illustration featuring cartoon versions of Lao Lao and Jordan, based on the reference photo. Lao Lao, a young woman of East Asian descent with long dark brown hair and round gold glasses, wearing a dark grey long-sleeved shirt, is depicted as a regal queen sitting on a throne made of a giant, steaming bowl of Chinese porridge (congee). She holds a boba tea like a royal scepter in one hand and delicately takes a bite of a giant banh mi sandwich with the other, a content and happy expression on her face. Jordan, a young man of Southeast Asian descent with spiky, textured dark brown hair and a big smile, wearing a maroon t-shirt, is on one knee beside the throne, presenting the banh mi to her on a silver platter with a comically adoring and subservient look. The entire scene has a soft, lighthearted feel with flowing colors, artistic paint splatters, and a visible paper texture.

Centered on the card, in a beautiful, readable handwritten cursive script, is the text:
"Happy Birthday to my Queen"

- Reference photos provided for character creation
- Characters should only appear on the front cover
- Transform real people into artistic cartoon/illustrated versions matching the style
- Maintain recognizable features while adapting to the artistic style
